commit.message: pre1.0.4-6: Updated the README and other files to refer to <https://slrn.info/>.
pre1.0.4-5: Corrected another bug int processing conditional expressions in custom format string.
pre1.0.4-4: The generic_article_as_string was not always returning a malloced string as required, causing an invalid free by the caller.
pre1.0.4-3: Corrected a bug affecting conditional expressions embedded in custom header strings
pre1.0.4-2: -lgnutls-openssl also needs -lgnutls
pre1.0.4-1: If getaddrinfo fails to produce a FQDN, then fallback to gethostbyname.
Version 1.0.3 released.
pre1.0.3-16: In the rfc1522_encode_word function, max_nbytes was not being properly limit checked
pre1.0.3-15: Updates for mingw and cygwin 32 and 64 bit systems
pre1.0.3-14: Removed compilation date info for a reproducible build.
pre1.0.3-13: Updated copyright years for upcoming release
pre1.0.3-12: Use labs instead of abs for long integers
pre1.0.3-11: If gnutls is used, do not use SSL_CTX_set_options.
pre1.0.3-10: If a mime article has already been base64/QP decoded, do not do it again.
pre1.0.3-9: Updated Danish translation
pre1.0.3-8: Added largefile support for 32 bit Unix systems
pre1.0.3-7: Use macro from autoconf archive to detect socket libs instead of relying upon X_EXTRA_LIBS
pre1.0.3-6: macros/mime.sl: In replace_article_with_mime_obj, also decode quoted-printable/base64.

pre1.0.3-5: 5. src/post.c: The reject_long_lines option was not working as documented.

Setting it to 0 had no effect when netiquette_warnings was set to a
non-zero value.
pre1.0.3-4: My previous commit introduced a typo.
pre1.0.3-3: Disable support for SSLv3, which is vulnerable to POODLE attacks.

pre1.0.3-2: After performing a characteset conversion on an article line, call it again to process the newline character.

Doing this resets the state for some conversion types.
pre1.0.3-1: A quoted-string in the display portion of an address was not being marked as allowing mime-encoded text.
Version 1.0.2 released
pre1.0.2 change 25: Do not remove po/*.gmo files if msgmerge is not installed.
pre1.0.2 change 24: slang 2.2.3 or later required
pre1.0.2 change 23: updated configure scripts
pre1.0.2 change 22: NEWS file added with release notes
pre1.0.2 change 21: Update copyright year
pre1.0.2 change 20: Strip \001 highlight indicator from messages when not in fullscreen mode.
